# Version Concept

> **Note**: This is a reference file. The authoritative documentation is in `.claude/agents/version-concept.md`.

**Model Assignment**: Opus 4.5 (git operations with conventional commits)
**Cost per Action**: ~$0.003
**State Location**: `data/versions/`
**Never Calls**: No other concepts (pure git operations)

## Quick Reference

### Actions
- `commit(impl_id, review_id)` - Creates a git commit
- `branch(story_id)` - Creates a feature branch
- `tag(version)` - Creates a version tag

### State File Format
```yaml
# data/versions/version-{id}.yaml
version_id: "version-001"
impl_id: "impl-001"
status: "committed"  # pending, committed, pushed, tagged
summary: "One-line summary"

details:
  branch: "feature/story-001-description"
  commit_hash: "abc123"
  commit_message: "feat(scope): description"
  files_changed: []
  metadata:
    created_at: "ISO-8601"
    concept: "version"
    model: "opus"
```

### Integration
- **Triggered by**: `quality-to-version` sync when quality.status="approved"
- **Triggers**: Workflow completion (no downstream concepts)

